cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE 

This paper deals with optimizing the performance of OpenCL programs on GPUs, which falls under the category of Parallel Computing (cs.PF). The use of machine learning to make decisions about optimization also suggests a possible fit for Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the use of programming languages and compilers to implement the optimization, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of synthetic and real benchmarks to train and test the model, which suggests a possible fit for Software Engineering (cs.SE).
